title: Fun game, few negatives.
text: Subway Surfers is honestly a very addicting game and I often find myself going to it when I‚Äôm bored. I love its fast paced gameplay and all the other little events they do to spice the game up and keep it entertaining. However, there is one VERY upsetting thing that happened yesterday. I have been saving my keys and almost had one hundred and getting keys is quite hard to get. There is this new character who costs around 77 keys I believe and I accidentally clicked on the button that you click to buy it, and it made me purchase the character. It didn‚Äôt give me any options asking if I was sure, and I believe this should be added. And it doesn‚Äôt help that this is a character I wouldn‚Äôt particularly buy on my own. It isn‚Äôt anything bad about the character, but it just isn‚Äôt my style and I believe it‚Äôs on the more masculine side which of course is alright, but I have a preference for female skins sense I‚Äôm a female myself. Another issue is that the character Im issuing won‚Äôt move to where I swipe during a run. I‚Äôll be at a good 150,000 and then I‚Äôll try to swipe to the right to avoid an obstacle and it won‚Äôt move, resulting in me getting caught by the police or getting hit by a train or whatever that obstacle was. I don‚Äôt know if this is something I‚Äôm doing, or if it is an issue with the games touch tracking but it gets quite annoying. Overall, a fun, addictive game that just needs a few tweaks just like any other game.
